    contentEn: `<h2>Avoid Common Mistakes</h2><p>Selling furniture can be profitable if done right. Finding a trusted used furniture store in Jeddah helps you avoid five common mistakes.</p><h2>First Mistake: Quick Sale</h2><p>Many sell to the first buyer without researching true value. This causes 30-40% loss. When looking for used furniture prices in Jeddah, compare multiple offers.</p><h3>Solution</h3><ul><li>Contact multiple specialists for comparison</li><li>Research similar prices</li><li>Consult trusted experts</li></ul><h2>Second Mistake: Neglecting Cleaning</h2><p>Dirty furniture drops 20-25% in price. When visiting used furniture stores, present clean furniture.</p><h3>Solution</h3><ul><li>Deep clean with appropriate products</li><li>Fix loose screws</li><li>Remove odors with natural fresheners</li><li>Arrange pillows beautifully</li></ul><h2>Third Mistake: Poor Photography</h2><p>Blurry photos reduce selling chances at good price. This affects the furniture buying price in Jeddah.</p><h3>Solution</h3><ul><li>Shoot during daytime in natural light</li><li>Take photos from multiple angles</li><li>Photograph defects clearly</li><li>Use modern camera</li></ul><h2>Fourth Mistake: Unknown Value</h2><p>Overpricing or underpricing both harm sales. This balance matters when buying used furniture in Jeddah.</p><h3>Solution</h3><ul><li>Determine furniture age</li><li>Evaluate material type</li><li>Research similar prices</li><li>Calculate repair costs</li></ul><h2>Fifth Mistake: Unreliable Buyers</h2><p>When calling trusted furniture store numbers, avoid unserious buyers.</p><h3>Solution</h3><ul><li>Ask for security deposit</li><li>Don't accept unverified checks</li><li>Deal with reputable specialists</li><li>Document everything in writing</li></ul><h2>Conclusion</h2><p>Selling to trusted specialists is the best choice. Call <strong>+966 55 978 1023</strong> for instant offer.</p>`,
